{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":833,"text":"So in 2011, I altered my name"},{"time":4255,"text":"so that I could participate\nin Far Right youth camp in Hungary."},{"time":8794,"text":"I was doing a PhD looking at\nyouth political socialization --"},{"time":13184,"text":"why young people were developing\npolitical ideologies"},{"time":16279,"text":"in a post-communist setting,"},{"time":18313,"text":"and I saw that a lot\nof young people I was talking to"},{"time":21570,"text":"were joining the Far Right,"},{"time":23194,"text":"and this was astounding to me."},{"time":25374,"text":"So I wanted to enroll in this youth camp"},{"time":27693,"text":"to get a better understanding\nof why people were joining."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30853,"text":"So a colleague enrolled me,"},{"time":32434,"text":"and my last name sounds\na little bit too Jewish."},{"time":35680,"text":"So Erin got turned into Iréna,"},{"time":38449,"text":"and Saltman got turned into Sós,"},{"time":40673,"text":"which means \"salty\" in Hungarian."},{"time":43618,"text":"And in Hungarian,\nyour last name goes first,"},{"time":45952,"text":"so my James Bond name\nturned into \"Salty Irena,\""},{"time":50390,"text":"which is not something\nI would have naturally chosen for myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54280,"text":"But going to this camp,"},{"time":56211,"text":"I was further shocked to realize\nthat it was actually really fun."},{"time":61180,"text":"They talked very little about politics."},{"time":63419,"text":"It was mostly learning how to ride horses,"},{"time":66456,"text":"shooting a bow and arrow,"},{"time":68348,"text":"live music at night,"},{"time":70059,"text":"free food and alcohol,"},{"time":72052,"text":"also some air-gun target practice"},{"time":74942,"text":"using mainstream politicians'\nfaces as targets."},{"time":78620,"text":"And this seemed like a very,\nactually, friendly, inclusive group"},{"time":82371,"text":"until you started talking or mentioning\nanything to do with the Roma population,"},{"time":87808,"text":"Jewish people or immigrants,"},{"time":90094,"text":"and then the discourse would become\nvery hate-based very quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94843,"text":"So it led me into my work now,"},{"time":97677,"text":"where we pose the question,"},{"time":100082,"text":"\"Why do people join\nviolent extremist movements,"},{"time":103146,"text":"and how do we effectively\ncounter these processes?\""},{"time":106573,"text":"In the aftermath of horrible\natrocities and attacks"},{"time":109888,"text":"in places like Belgium, France,\nbut all over the world,"},{"time":113275,"text":"sometimes it's easier for us to think,"},{"time":115132,"text":"\"Well, these must be sociopaths,"},{"time":117101,"text":"these must be naturally\nviolent individuals."},{"time":120189,"text":"They must have something wrong\nwith their upbringing.\""},{"time":122809,"text":"And what's really tragic"},{"time":124920,"text":"is that oftentimes there's no one profile."},{"time":127135,"text":"Many people come\nfrom educated backgrounds,"},{"time":130413,"text":"different socioeconomic backgrounds,"},{"time":132533,"text":"men and women, different ages,"},{"time":135405,"text":"some with families, some single."},{"time":137707,"text":"So why? What is this allure?"},{"time":140386,"text":"And this is what\nI want to talk you through,"},{"time":142459,"text":"as well as how do we\nchallenge this in a modern era?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":146711,"text":"We do know, through research,"},{"time":148218,"text":"that there are quite a number\nof different things"},{"time":150598,"text":"that affect somebody's\nprocess of radicalization,"},{"time":153973,"text":"and we categorize these\ninto push and pull factors."},{"time":156767,"text":"And these are pretty much similar\nfor Far Right, neo-Nazi groups"},{"time":160204,"text":"all the way to Islamist extremist\nand terrorist groups."},{"time":163663,"text":"And push factors are basically\nwhat makes you vulnerable"},{"time":167545,"text":"to a process of radicalization,"},{"time":169427,"text":"to joining a violent extremist group."},{"time":171657,"text":"And these can be\na lot of different things,"},{"time":173807,"text":"but roughly, a sense of alienation,\na sense of isolation,"},{"time":177744,"text":"questioning your own identity,"},{"time":179919,"text":"but also feeling that your in-group\nis under attack,"},{"time":182769,"text":"and your in group might be based\non a nationality or an ethnicity"},{"time":186586,"text":"or a religion,"},{"time":187936,"text":"and feeling that larger powers around you\nare doing nothing to help."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192075,"text":"Now, push factors alone\ndo not make you a violent extremist,"},{"time":195520,"text":"because if that were the fact,"},{"time":196974,"text":"those same factors would go\ntowards a group like the Roma population,"},{"time":200268,"text":"and they're not\na violently mobilized group."},{"time":203073,"text":"So we have to look at the pull factors."},{"time":205384,"text":"What are these violent\nextremist organizations offering"},{"time":208718,"text":"that other groups are not offering?"},{"time":210687,"text":"And actually, this is usually\nvery positive things,"},{"time":213274,"text":"very seemingly empowering things,"},{"time":215315,"text":"such as brotherhood and sisterhood"},{"time":217802,"text":"and a sense of belonging,"},{"time":219160,"text":"as well as giving somebody\na spiritual purpose,"},{"time":222058,"text":"a divine purpose\nto build a utopian society"},{"time":225797,"text":"if their goals can be met,"},{"time":227742,"text":"but also a sense of empowerment\nand adventure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230517,"text":"When we look\nat foreign terrorist fighters,"},{"time":232584,"text":"we see young men\nwith the wind in their hair"},{"time":235299,"text":"out in the desert\nand women going to join them"},{"time":237869,"text":"to have nuptials out in the sunset."},{"time":240534,"text":"It's very romantic, and you become a hero."},{"time":244378,"text":"For both men and women,\nthat's the propaganda being given."},{"time":247667,"text":"So what extremist groups are very good at"},{"time":250333,"text":"is taking a very complicated,\nconfusing, nuanced world"},{"time":255183,"text":"and simplifying that world\ninto black and white,"},{"time":258450,"text":"good and evil."},{"time":259684,"text":"And you become what is good,"},{"time":261589,"text":"challenging what is evil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264541,"text":"So I want to talk a little bit\nabout ISIS, Daesh,"},{"time":268429,"text":"because they have been a game changer\nin how we look at these processes,"},{"time":272831,"text":"and through a lot of the material\nand their tactics."},{"time":276061,"text":"They're very much a modern movement."},{"time":278925,"text":"One of the aspects is the internet\nand the usage of social media,"},{"time":283434,"text":"as we've all seen in headlines\ntweeting and videos of beheadings."},{"time":287840,"text":"But the internet alone\ndoes not radicalize you."},{"time":290339,"text":"The internet is a tool."},{"time":291570,"text":"You don't go online shopping for shoes"},{"time":293450,"text":"and accidentally become a jihadist."},{"time":295793,"text":"However, what the Internet\ndoes do is it is a catalyst."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299206,"text":"It provides tools and scale and rapidity"},{"time":303349,"text":"that doesn't exist elsewhere."},{"time":304881,"text":"And with ISIS, all of a sudden,"},{"time":307366,"text":"this idea of a cloaked, dark figure\nof a jihadist changed for us."},{"time":312708,"text":"All of a sudden,\nwe were in their kitchens."},{"time":314787,"text":"We saw what they were eating for dinner."},{"time":316810,"text":"They were tweeting."},{"time":317985,"text":"We had foreign terrorist fighters\ntweeting in their own languages."},{"time":321167,"text":"We had women going out there\ntalking about their wedding day,"},{"time":324143,"text":"about the births of their children."},{"time":325914,"text":"We had gaming culture, all of a sudden,"},{"time":327835,"text":"and references\nto Grand Theft Auto being made."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331471,"text":"So all of a sudden, they were homey."},{"time":333956,"text":"They became human."},{"time":335131,"text":"And the problem\nis that trying to counter it,"},{"time":337369,"text":"lots of governments\nand social media companies"},{"time":339703,"text":"just tried to censor."},{"time":340878,"text":"How do we get rid of terrorist content?"},{"time":342893,"text":"And it became a cat-and-mouse game"},{"time":344572,"text":"where we would see accounts taken down\nand they'd just come back up,"},{"time":347800,"text":"and an arrogance around somebody\nhaving a 25th account"},{"time":350937,"text":"and material that was\ndisseminated everywhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354055,"text":"But we also saw a dangerous trend --"},{"time":356100,"text":"violent extremists know the rules\nand regulations of social media, too."},{"time":361132,"text":"So we would see a banal\nconversation with a recruiter"},{"time":365156,"text":"start on a mainstream platform,"},{"time":367153,"text":"and at the point\nat which that conversation"},{"time":369258,"text":"was going to become illegal,"},{"time":370622,"text":"they would jump to a smaller,\nless regulated,"},{"time":373147,"text":"more encrypted platform."},{"time":374794,"text":"So all of a sudden, we couldn't\ntrack where that conversation went."},{"time":378351,"text":"So this is a problem with censorship,"},{"time":380237,"text":"which is why we need to develop\nalternatives to censorship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384035,"text":"ISIS is also a game-changer\nbecause it's state-building."},{"time":387409,"text":"It's not just recruiting combatants;"},{"time":389545,"text":"it's trying to build a state."},{"time":391431,"text":"And what that means is all of a sudden,"},{"time":393395,"text":"your recruitment model is much more broad."},{"time":395419,"text":"You're not just trying to get fighters --"},{"time":397492,"text":"now you need architects, engineers,\naccountants, hackers and women."},{"time":401782,"text":"We've actually seen\na huge increase of women going"},{"time":404196,"text":"in the last 24, but especially 12 months."},{"time":407719,"text":"Some countries, one in four\nof the people going over to join"},{"time":410632,"text":"are now women."},{"time":411895,"text":"And so, this really changes"},{"time":413287,"text":"who we're trying to counter\nthis process with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416679,"text":"Now, not all doom and gloom."},{"time":418354,"text":"So the rest I'd like to talk about\nsome of the positive things"},{"time":421338,"text":"and the new innovation in trying\nto prevent and counter violent extremism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425206,"text":"Preventing is very different\nthan countering,"},{"time":427503,"text":"and actually, you can think of it\nin medical terms."},{"time":430083,"text":"So preventative medicine is,"},{"time":432329,"text":"how do we make it\nso you are naturally resilient"},{"time":435527,"text":"to this process of radicalization,"},{"time":438051,"text":"whereas that is going to be different"},{"time":439937,"text":"if somebody is already showing\na symptom or a sign"},{"time":442620,"text":"of belonging to a violent\nextremist ideology."},{"time":445525,"text":"And so in preventative measures,"},{"time":447096,"text":"we're talking more\nabout really broad groups of people"},{"time":449811,"text":"and exposure to ideas"},{"time":451652,"text":"to make them resilient."},{"time":453443,"text":"Whereas it's very different"},{"time":454983,"text":"if somebody is starting to question\nand agree with certain things online,"},{"time":458832,"text":"and it's also very different\nif somebody already has a swastika tattoo"},{"time":462705,"text":"and is very much embedded within a group."},{"time":464777,"text":"How do you reach them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":466785,"text":"So I'd like to go through three examples\nof each one of those levels"},{"time":470491,"text":"and talk you through"},{"time":471730,"text":"what some of the new ways\nof engaging with people are becoming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475374,"text":"One is \"Extreme Dialogue,\""},{"time":476811,"text":"and it's an educational program\nthat we helped develop."},{"time":479915,"text":"This one is from Canada,"},{"time":482320,"text":"and it's meant to create dialogues\nwithin a classroom setting,"},{"time":486439,"text":"using storytelling,"},{"time":487995,"text":"because violent extremism\ncan be very hard to try to explain,"},{"time":491170,"text":"especially to younger individuals."},{"time":493305,"text":"So we have a network of former extremists\nand survivors of extremism"},{"time":497242,"text":"that tell their stories through video\nand create question-giving to classrooms,"},{"time":501203,"text":"to start a conversation about the topic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503530,"text":"These two examples show Christianne,"},{"time":506086,"text":"who lost her son,"},{"time":507261,"text":"who radicalized and died\nfighting for ISIS,"},{"time":509778,"text":"and Daniel is a former neo-Nazi"},{"time":511469,"text":"who was an extremely violent neo-Nazi,"},{"time":513851,"text":"and they pose questions about their lives\nand where they're at and regret,"},{"time":518033,"text":"and force a classroom\nto have a dialogue around it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521175,"text":"Now, looking at that middle range\nof individuals,"},{"time":524184,"text":"actually, we need a lot\nof civil society voices."},{"time":526907,"text":"How do you interact with people\nthat are looking for information online,"},{"time":530376,"text":"that are starting to toy with an ideology,"},{"time":532742,"text":"that are doing those searching\nidentity questions?"},{"time":535830,"text":"How do we provide alternatives for that?"},{"time":537996,"text":"And that's when we combine\nlarge groups of civil society voices"},{"time":541410,"text":"with creatives, techies,\napp developers, artists, comedians,"},{"time":545965,"text":"and we can create really specified content"},{"time":548672,"text":"and actually, online, disseminate it\nto very strategic audiences."},{"time":552990,"text":"So one example would be\ncreating a satirical video"},{"time":555817,"text":"which makes fun of Islamophobia,"},{"time":558340,"text":"and targeting it\nto 15- to 20-year-olds online"},{"time":562300,"text":"that have an interest in white power music"},{"time":564571,"text":"and live specifically in Manchester."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566994,"text":"We can use these marketing tools\nto be very specific,"},{"time":570049,"text":"so that we know\nwhen somebody's viewing, watching"},{"time":572796,"text":"and engaging with that content,"},{"time":574309,"text":"it's not just the average person,\nit's not me or you --"},{"time":576963,"text":"it's a very specific audience\nthat we are looking to engage with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580704,"text":"Even more downstream, we developed\na pilot program called \"One to One,\""},{"time":584427,"text":"where we took former extremists"},{"time":586000,"text":"and we had them reach out directly\nto a group of labeled neofascists"},{"time":590888,"text":"as well as Islamist extremists,"},{"time":592536,"text":"and put direct messages through Facebook\nMessenger into their inbox, saying,"},{"time":596375,"text":"\"Hey, I see where you're going.\nI've been there."},{"time":598685,"text":"If you want to talk, I'm here.\""},{"time":600251,"text":"Now, we kind of expected death threats\nfrom this sort of interaction."},{"time":603529,"text":"It's a little alarming to have\na former neo-Nazi say, \"Hey, how are you?\""},{"time":607973,"text":"But actually, we found\nthat around 60 percent"},{"time":610204,"text":"of the people reached out to responded,"},{"time":612782,"text":"and of that, around another 60 percent\nhad sustained engagement,"},{"time":616891,"text":"meaning that they were\nhaving conversations"},{"time":618971,"text":"with the hardest people to reach\nabout what they were going through,"},{"time":622211,"text":"planting seeds of doubt"},{"time":623386,"text":"and giving them alternatives\nfor talking about these subjects,"},{"time":626402,"text":"and that's really important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629061,"text":"So what we're trying to do"},{"time":631308,"text":"is actually bring\nunlikely sectors to the table."},{"time":634237,"text":"We have amazing activists\nall over the world,"},{"time":636587,"text":"but oftentimes,\ntheir messages are not strategic"},{"time":638977,"text":"or they don't actually reach\nthe audiences they want to reach."},{"time":641907,"text":"So we work with networks\nof former extremists."},{"time":644170,"text":"We work with networks of young people\nin different parts of the world."},{"time":647623,"text":"And we work with them\nto bring the tech sector to the table"},{"time":650417,"text":"with artists and creatives\nand marketing expertise"},{"time":653259,"text":"so that we can actually have\na more robust and challenging of extremism"},{"time":658284,"text":"that works together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660074,"text":"So I would say\nthat if you are in the audience"},{"time":662678,"text":"and you happen to be a graphic designer,"},{"time":665401,"text":"a poet, a marketing expert,"},{"time":667607,"text":"somebody that works in PR,"},{"time":669540,"text":"a comedian --"},{"time":670917,"text":"you might not think\nthat this is your sector,"},{"time":673092,"text":"but actually, the skills\nthat you have right now"},{"time":675855,"text":"might be exactly what is needed"},{"time":677882,"text":"to help challenge extremism effectively."}]},{"cues":[{"time":680215,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":681390,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}